english:
  title: Congratulations on the Birth of a Daughter to Minister Chen of the Hanlin Academy
  author: Lee Yu-ji
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Chang'e herself has carved the moon to fashion a spirit—
    and sent it cradled to a cultured scholar's gate.
    Silk screens embroidered, damask curtains layered round,
    how many times has she been bathed in fragrant waters from a golden basin?
    Clouds rising from the peaks of Chu scatter like leaves in an instant,
    yet jade born in Lantian springs has roots that run far deeper.
    From this moment onward, blessing and abundance shall surely flow,
    as groves of jade and pearl trees spread across the endless sky.
  footnotes:
    - 'Chang''e (素娥): The moon goddess in Chinese mythology, here invoked to suggest the child''s celestial beauty and purity.'
    - 'Chu peaks and Lantian: References to legendary places of natural beauty and jade production, elevating the metaphor of the newborn''s worth.'
    - '余慶: A Confucian concept referring to inherited virtue and blessings that accumulate through generations, suggesting the child will bring lasting fortune to the family.'
